description.narrative: Progress was made towards a child-friendly and responsive social welfare and justice system as an integral part of the child protection system. This included the recognition of social welfare officers as a key part of the critical COVID-19 response team, resulting from UNICEF advocacy; capacity development of 150 police officers on the diversion guidelines in five districts; and an increased number of children being fast tracked in the justice system. Challenges included a weak normative framework for defining the workforce, lack of a supervision system, no system for licensing/accreditation and significant gaps in the social welfare workforce.; | Status:Met | As-of Date:13/01/2021
